,Recommended,643810,34955141,Posted: 14 September,all,TheHamster,"I have been eyeing fugl for a long time, and today I finally got to play it. Here is my experience so far. I played the game with an XBOX ONE controller via USB cable.REALLY GOOD!- Really beautiful music when it plays.- Really relaxing sounds, especially the sound of waves and the wind blowing.- Vibrant colors painting a beautiful world.- Lots of fish and creatues that are fun to spot.- Interesting highlights making you want to see what might be there.- Performance. I have an an i5-2500K CPU (3.3 ghz) and a gtx 970 GPU. Everything was butter smooth all the time.- A joy to find new biomes.- Playing as different creatures are fun. Ducks are fast, but hard to control when flying slow, butterflies pretty much the opposite.COULD BE BETTER...- You do not play 1st or 3rd person, but in ""bird♥♥♥♥♥quot; perspective. Simply said, I feel the camera is way too close to the bird. I'd prefer the camera a bit further away. And I would absolutely ADORE first person perspective.- It's currently a bit hard to land and take off. I'd prefer it to be easier. Also the bird flaps lake crazy when taking off. Would prefer a more slow, but powerfull flapping.- You ""become"" the birds and creatures you get close to for a short time, before turning back into your start bird. It is kind of cool sometimes, other times kind of irritating. I do not find it serene to become a flying monkey all the time. A skill to target and transform into the creates you see when YOU want to would be better (my opinion).- No reward for exploration. I don't expect much, but certain areas/spots should give a reward when you reach them. It could some interesting creatures to observe, a special view, some music you don't otherwise get to hear, a new ability, a piece of lore, , a nice little animation or scene, a mini game, or whatever.- More variation in the terrain generation. When you fly fast, things seem very similar. Points of interest, like an extra special create, a castle, and such would be nice.- Bird walking and sound animation. Right now you just hover in silence when you move on ground.IN SORE NEED OF IMPROVEMENT- Bugs. I often experienced the immidate surroundings around me disappearing. I could see things in the distance, but they would disaapear when I get close.- Crashes. I experienced it twice now.- A jump button. Srsly, I really missed that while on ground.- An introduction to the controls. You get a 5 second overview of the controls before the screen disappears. I'd like that to stay for a bit longer. Also, there was no mention that you can control the power of flaps by the amount of pressure you apply on the shoulder buttons.- The camera got stuck a couple of times.All in all, I would recommend getting this game, especially it costing next to nothing. Gameplay wise it has some way to go, and control/camera wise it could use a lot of improvement in my opinion. But seeing this is an early access game , I am in no doubt that this will all improve over time.I hope you and the developer(s) will find this review helpful. I can't wait to make this my go-to chill game after a long day of work, when it becomes a bit less frustrating to control your bird  ;)Best regards from Denmark.P.S. Please please PLEEEEEASE add first person perspective! :D"
