76561197987816691,Recommended,643810,35240984,Posted: 27 September,all,NoPantsMan,"Fugl is the true beauty of gamingIt's kind of hard to accurately express the feeling of Fugl, it is exactly as it describes itself. You play as a bird like creature that morphs fluidly between colours and shapes and you explore an ever morphing world of colour and shapes. The majesty is that it doesn't try to be more than that but it so perfectly captures the feeling of instinctive flight that you just want to go forever. If you've ever played something like Minecraft and rather than engage in building you set out and just explored what the engine would generate, Fugl is that but far more visually stimulating.*EARLY ACCESS NOTES*So here's the ugly bit, the game is still very much in early access - if your computer isn't at least a bit of beast there's no chance of the game running well. Temporarily there's a mode where the game pre-generates an environment to fly in if your computer isn't up to snuff but the developers are hoping to reduce the system requirements.*END EARLY ACCESS NOTES*There's also more content expected to be added so it's hard to say what the final form of the game will take precisely but put simply, if your computer can run it and you want an unforgettable game of pure experience, Fugl is here right now and you should buy it immediately."
